'''''Sword Coast Adventurer's Guide''''' is a regional sourcebook, by [[Wizards of the Coast]], set in the {{SmallCaps|[[Forgotten Realms]]}} using the ''[[Dungeons & Dragons]]'' 5th edition ruleset. It focuses on [[West Faerûn|west]] and [[northwest Faerûn]].{{cite web| url            = http://dnd.wizards.com/articles/news/scag| title          = Spice Up Your Story| accessdate     = | accessmonthday = July 23| accessyear     = 2015| author         = [[Greg Tito]]| last           = | first          = | authorlink     = | coauthors      = | date           = 2015-July-22| year           = | month          = | work           = | publisher      = [[Wizards of the Coast]]| pages          = | language       = | archiveurl     = | archivedate    = | quote          = }}

{{Quote|'''''WELCOME TO THE SWORD COAST'''''

''A region of the Forgotten Realms<sup>&reg;</sup>, the [[Sword Coast]] comprises shining paragons of civilization, perilous locales fraught with evil, and, encompassing them all, a wilderness that offers an explorer both vast opportunity and great danger.

The'' Sword Coast Adventurer's Guide&trade; ''is a valuable resource for Dungeon Masters and players alike. In addition to describing the peoples and places of the Sword Coast, the book contains a plethora of new character options to intrigue and inspire every adventuring party.''

''For use with the fifth edition ''[[Player's Handbook 5th edition|Player's Handbook]]''<sup>&reg;</sup>, ''[[Monster Manual 5th edition|Monster Manual]]''<sup>&reg;</sup>, and ''[[Dungeon Master's Guide 5th edition|Dungeon Master's Guide]]''<sup>&reg;</sup>, this book provides the setting, story, and character options needed to participate in a D&D game anywhere along the Sword Coast of [[Faerûn]].''}}

